<titles class="MCRMetaLangText" heritable="false" notinherit="false"><title xml:lang="en" inherited="0" form="plain">Mäṣḥafä gǝnzät “Book of the Funeral Ritual” / Ṣälotä śǝryätä ḫaṭiʾat “Prayer of absolution of Sins”</title>
</titles>
<shortcontents class="MCRMetaLangText" heritable="false" notinherit="false"><shortcontent xml:lang="en" inherited="0" form="plain">I) Mäṣḥafä gǝnzät “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 3ra-122vb)&#13;
- Introduction (fols. 3ra-5rb)&#13;
- Discourse of St. Athanasius on death (fols. 9va-16vb)&#13;
- Mäṣḥaf zä-wäḍʾat ʾǝm-ʾIyärusalem “Book that Came from Jerusalem” (fols. 17ra-22ra)&#13;
- Homily by St. Jacob of Serug for the funeral of priests and deacons (fols. 65va-68ra)&#13;
- Homily by ʾabba Sälama, Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols. 80ra-83va)&#13;
- Lǝfafä ṣǝdq “Bandlet of Righteousness” (fols. 85vb-88vb)&#13;
- Mängädä sämay “Journey to Heaven” (fols. 88vb-89va)&#13;
- Antiphons (ʾaryam, kǝśtät, sälam, mäzmur) (fols. 28ra-29ra, 43vb-44vb, 48ra-va, 49va-51ra, 53rb, 55ra-56ra, 57ra, 58va-59ra, 61rb-va, 64vb)&#13;
II) Ṣälotä śǝryätä ḫaṭiʾat “Prayer of Absolution of Sins” (fols. 123ra-126rb), (cp. EMML 427(9))&#13;
&#13;
Additiones 1-2.</shortcontent>
</shortcontents>
